            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In relation to neovim/nvim-lspconfig#3788\r\n\r\nI have a table of servers like so:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal servers = {\r\n  asm_lsp = { ... },\r\n  ast_grep = { ... },\r\n  harper_ls = { ... },\r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\nover which I iterate:\r\n```\r\nfor name, conf in pairs(servers) do\r\n  vim.lsp.config(name, conf)\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow would look `merge_behavior` function that removes `filetypes` field from e.g. ast-grep and Harper servers (to activate them for all filetypes) and also prevents nvim-lspconfig or other config from repopulating it?",
